The paper presents new distributed algorithms for constructing a Steiner Forest in the CONGEST model, which is a well-studied problem in distributed computing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also involves graph algorithms and network optimization, which are topics covered in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with network communication and routing, which are relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves approximation algorithms and complexity theory, which are topics covered in the Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves game theory and optimization, which are relevant to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
